<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<definitions xmlns="http://www.omg.org/spec/BPMN/20100524/MODEL"
             xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
             xmlns:flowable="http://flowable.org/bpmn"
             targetNamespace="http://d2os.com/bpmn"
             id="d2os-review-gate-definitions">

  <!--
    Review Gate subprocess (Phase 5, T012, US1, research R1, FR-001). A STANDALONE ProcessDefinition
    published as the SUBPROCESS DefinitionAsset `subprocess.review-gate` (CatalogSeedLoader.seedPhase5)
    and invoked as a callActivity from case workflows (T015: initiation-v3, assessment-v2) — one
    definition, reused by reference across case types (R1), never re-implemented per workflow.

    Shape: start -> gate-decision (userTask) -> end. The userTask's `create` taskListener
    (gateTaskBridge, GateTaskBridge.java) opens the GateInstance row and correlates engine_task_id;
    GateService.decide() later completes this SAME task via TaskService.complete(engineTaskId,
    {gateDecision: verb}) once the human decision (APPROVE/REJECT/REQUEST_CHANGES) is recorded as a
    Decision + AuditEntry (governance module, Flowable-free). `gateDecision` becomes a variable on this
    subprocess's execution once the task completes, which the CALLING process's callActivity
    `flowable:out` mapping reads back to route on the verb (T015) — this process itself does not
    branch on the verb; it is a pure reusable wait-and-report subprocess.

    Process-variable contract this subprocess READS (set by the caller's callActivity `flowable:in`
    mappings, T015 — not by this file, since T012 has no caller wired yet): workspaceId,
    caseInstanceId, gateType, gateDefinitionKey, gateDefinitionVersion, inputsRef, and optionally
    subjectArtifactRevisionId / escalationPolicyKey / escalationPolicyVersion (GateTaskBridge's exact
    variable contract). It WRITES `gateDecision` (set by GateService.decide's engine-release call),
    read back out by the caller's callActivity `flowable:out` mapping.

    Non-interrupting boundary timer (research R4, Phase 6/US4, T032/T033): fires into
    `timerEscalationDelegate` (TimerEscalationDelegate.java, orchestration), which calls governance's
    `TimerFiredHandler` — records an `escalation_activation` row, notifies the resolved role, and emits
    `GATE_ESCALATION_FIRED`. cancelActivity="false" is the load-bearing bit: the gate userTask is
    completely untouched when this fires — no transition authority (Principle V), by construction, not
    discipline; TimerFiredHandler's own code never mutates GateInstance status or the engine task
    either. The fixed P3D duration is a placeholder matching the seeded `escalation-policy.default`
    step-0 duration (CatalogSeedLoader) until a future pass pins the gate's own
    escalation_policy_key/version dynamically into this timer's own duration expression.
  -->
  <process id="review-gate" name="Review Gate" isExecutable="true">

    <startEvent id="start"/>
    <sequenceFlow id="g0" sourceRef="start" targetRef="gate-decision"/>

    <userTask id="gate-decision" name="Reviewer Decision">
      <extensionElements>
        <flowable:taskListener event="create" delegateExpression="${gateTaskBridge}"/>
      </extensionElements>
    </userTask>
    <sequenceFlow id="g1" sourceRef="gate-decision" targetRef="end"/>

    <boundaryEvent id="gate-decision-sla-timer" attachedToRef="gate-decision" cancelActivity="false">
      <timerEventDefinition>
        <timeDuration>P3D</timeDuration>
      </timerEventDefinition>
    </boundaryEvent>
    <sequenceFlow id="g2" sourceRef="gate-decision-sla-timer" targetRef="timer-escalation"/>
    <serviceTask id="timer-escalation" name="Record SLA Escalation"
                 flowable:delegateExpression="${timerEscalationDelegate}"/>
    <sequenceFlow id="g3" sourceRef="timer-escalation" targetRef="timer-escalation-marker"/>
    <endEvent id="timer-escalation-marker" name="SLA timer handled"/>

    <endEvent id="end"/>
  </process>
</definitions>
